Andrew JACKSON, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 5822. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 10, 1930. John H. Cook, of Clarksdale, Miss. (Cook & Ascough, of Clarksdale, Miss., on the brief), for appellant. Lester G. Pant, U. S. Atty., of Holly Springs, Miss.

Before BRYAN and FOSTER, Circuit Judges, and GRUBB, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
